The All Saints Anglican Church, Montgomery Road, Yaba, Lagos, has rolled out drums for its 90th-anniversary celebrations scheduled for Sunday, June 12 to Sunday, June 19, 2022. According to Dr Sesan Onabowale, Chairman of the 90th Anniversary Planning Committee, the programme of events is as follows, Sunday, June 12, the opening service services will hold at 7 am, 8:45 am and 10.30 am. This will be followed by the anniversary health awareness and screening; Day 2, Monday, June 13, will feature the variety show and drama by the women’s and girls’ organisation and the Sunday school pupils, with the theme: “God our everlasting strength,” at 12 noon. Day 3, Tuesday, June 14, a tournament organized by the parish youth council will commence. Day 4 Wednesday, June 15, anniversary lecture and symposium with the theme: “God Our Everlasting Strength, Church of the Future and Saints of the Next Decade. The guest lecturer is Rt. Rev. Prof. Dapo Asaju, the Bishop Theologian and the Bishop of Ilesha Diocese, Church of Nigeria, under the distinguished chairmanship of Prof. Olufemi Otubanjo (PhD.) Day 5, Thursday, June 16, there will be a visit to the Old People’s Home and the Orphanage by 10. am and at 5 pm, we will commence the anniversary revival themed: “The Ever-Faithful God,”, Revivalist is Vel. Niyi Ageshi of the Lagos Diocese. On day 6, Friday, June 17, all the sporting tournaments will be rounded-off while in the evening, the anniversary revival will be rounded-off. POLL On day 7, Saturday, June 18, there will be the book launch, titled: “The Heritage of Faith: The Story of All Saints Anglican Church, Yaba”. Also the same day, there will be a fund-raising for parish legacy projects and merit awards thereafter. While on Sunday, June 19, will witness the grand finale and the 90th-anniversary founders’ day thanksgiving by 9:30 am.